The Scheduler (PopulateJob):
This is the "Trigger" for your data conversion.
Logic: It will execute the code in com.bac.populatejob every night at 9:05 PM (0 5 21 * * ?).
GitOps Role: Because enabled: false is set, the job is "dormant." In a GitOps workflow,
you would keep it disabled in your repository and only flip it to true via a Pull Request
when you are ready to start the migration or synchronization in a specific environment.

Field            Value / Meaning
job-class        populatejob — This is the Java class containing the logic to fetch data from MongoDB (StepV2) and prepare it for SQL.
cron-expression  0 5 21 * * ? — This job is scheduled to run every day at 9:05 PM.
enabled: false   Critical: The job is currently deactivated. It will not run automatically unless this is changed to true.
job-group        f.step — Used to categorize jobs in the Quartz monitor/database.

ferguson:
